-- Jefferies Hires Alexander, 5 CLSA Staff for Asia Sales, Trading Research
-- Finbarr Flynn
-- 2010-07-29T02:15:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-29/jefferies-hires-alexander-5-clsa-staff-for-asia-sales-trading-research.html

          
          
             Jefferies Group Inc. , the New-York
based investment bank, hired  Michael   Alexander  as chief
executive officer of its Asia unit and five other CLSA employees
to build sales and trading, and equity research in the region.  
 Alexander will join the company in October from Credit
Agricole SA’s CLSA unit, Jefferies said in a statement today.
Alexander has 25 years of experience in sales and trading and
will be based in Hong Kong.  
 Jefferies  plans to hire additional sales and trading, and
research personnel in the region in the coming months including
 Chris Shute , Tom Halliwell, Phil Lord, Michael Collett, and
Quinn Bolon from CLSA. It is also hiring  Nilesh Jasani  and Grant
Williams formerly of Credit Suisse Group AG, Jefferies said in
today’s release.  
 Jefferies has increased staff by more than 25 percent in
two years, as it targets growth in Hong Kong, India, Japan,
Singapore, Korea and Taiwan, it said.  
